title: What is Free Trade?
description:
In 1955, free-trade advocate Dr. Lewis E. Lloyd wrote a book on how eight conditions must be met to have free and fair trade. What he discovered changed his view of free trade, especially in regard to free trade agreements and the welfare of America. Are you in favor of merging America with other countries?

Contact Congress in opposition to the Trans-Pacific Partnership: https://www.votervoice.net/JBS/campaigns/40031/respond
